    "content": "<!--StartFragment--><p data-path-to-node=\"1\">In today's digital age, many government services have moved online for greater accessibility and convenience. One such vital service is the ability to file a First Information Report (FIR) online. This process, often called an \"e-FIR,\" allows citizens to report non-cognizable offenses and other complaints directly through a state police's official web portal, saving time and effort.</p><p data-path-to-node=\"2\">This guide will walk you through the simple process of filing an FIR online, step-by-step, using a series of helpful infographics.</p><h3>Overview of the Online FIR Process</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Before we dive into the details, let's take a quick look at the overall process. The entire procedure can be broken down into a few simple steps, as shown in the flowchart below.</p><p data-path-to-node=\"5\"></p><div class=\"attachment-container generated-images\"><response-element class=\"\" ng-version=\"0.0.0-PLACEHOLDER\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><generated-image _nghost-ng-c1105230103=\"\" class=\"ng-star-inserted\" style=\"aspect-ratio: auto;\"><div _ngcontent-ng-c1105230103=\"\" class=\"loader\"></div><single-image _ngcontent-ng-c1105230103=\"\" class=\"generated-image\" _nghost-ng-c3119414750=\"\" jslog=\"185864;track:generic_click,impression,attention;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_b1e4d790c9896c8d&quot;,&quot;c_ebfd8f8b6e2d3ec5&quot;,null,&quot;rc_d0def4216bccb78b&quot;,null,null,&quot;en&quot;,null,1,null,null,1,1]];mutable:true\" data-is-interactive=\"false\" data-image-attachment-index=\"0\" data-hveid=\"0\" decode-data-ved=\"1\" data-ved=\"0CAAQiKwLahcKEwig1-O0md6RAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQMQ\"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3119414750=\"\" replace-fife-images-at-export=\"\" class=\"image-container replace-fife-images-at-export ng-star-inserted\"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3119414750=\"\" class=\"overlay-container ng-star-inserted\"><!--StartFragment--><h3>Step 1: Find Your State's Police Portal</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"9\">The first step is to locate the official online portal of your state or city's police department. You can easily do this by performing a simple search on your preferred search engine. For example, you can search for \"Online FIR [Your State Name] Police\".</p><h3>Step 2: Register or Login to the Portal</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><!--StartFragment--><!--EndFragment--></p><p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Once you have accessed the portal, you will need to create an account if you are a new user. If you have already registered, you can simply log in with your credentials. Registration typically requires basic personal details like your name, address, and contact number.</p><h3>Step 3: Fill the Online Complaint Form</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><!--StartFragment--><!--EndFragment--></p><p data-path-to-node=\"18\">After logging in, navigate to the \"Online Complaint\" or \"e-FIR\" section. You will be presented with a digital form where you need to provide detailed information about the incident. This includes the date, time, and location of the incident, a description of what happened, and any known details about the suspect(s) or witnesses.</p><h3>Step 4: Upload Necessary Documents</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><!--StartFragment--><!--EndFragment--></p><p data-path-to-node=\"22\">To support your complaint, you will need to upload certain documents. This typically includes a scanned copy of your government-issued ID proof (like Aadhaar card, Voter ID, or Passport) and any other supporting documents related to the incident (e.g., photographs, medical reports, or a written complaint).</p><h3>Step 5: Submit and Receive e-FIR Number</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><!--StartFragment--><!--EndFragment--></p><p data-path-to-node=\"26\">Once you have filled in all the required details and uploaded the necessary documents, you can review your application and submit it. Upon successful submission, you will immediately receive a unique e-FIR number on the screen and via SMS/email. This number is crucial for tracking the progress of your complaint.</p><h3>Conclusion</h3><p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><!--StartFragment--><!--EndFragment--></p><p data-path-to-node=\"30\">Filing an FIR online is a straightforward process that can be completed from the comfort of your home. By following these simple steps, you can ensure your complaint is registered with the police and that you have a record of it for future reference. Remember to keep your e-FIR number safe, as you can use it to track the status of your complaint online at any time. This digital initiative is a significant step towards making the justice system more accessible and efficient for everyone.</p><!--EndFragment--><!----><!----><button _ngcontent-ng-c3119414750=\"\" class=\"image-button ng-star-inserted\" jslog=\"181501;track:generic_click,impression;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_b1e4d790c9896c8d&quot;,&quot;c_ebfd8f8b6e2d3ec5&quot;,null,&quot;rc_d0def4216bccb78b&quot;,null,null,&quot;en&quot;,null,1,null,null,1,1]];mutable:true\"></button></div></div></single-image></generated-image></response-element></div><p></p><!--EndFragment-->"
